THE SPREAD OPERATOR [...]

SHALLOW COPY - references original 

when used with array [...arrayName] -> creates a shallow copy of an array 
- creates new array (triggers RE_RENDER)- elements of new array are references to same objects of original array 
- changes 
    changes in the copy won't affect the original 
    changes to objects or arrays within the copy will affect original 

REACT relies on immutability to determine when to RE-RENDER
    - immutability 


    // Original array with primitive and object elements
const original = [1, "hello", { name: "Alice" }, [10, 20]];

    // Create a shallow copy
const copy = [...original];

    // Modifying primitive values
    // DOES NOT MODIFY ORIGINAL
copy[0] = 99;
copy[1] = "world";

console.log(original[0]); // Output: 1
console.log(copy[0]);     // Output: 99
console.log(original[1]); // Output: "hello"
console.log(copy[1]);     // Output: "world"

    // Modifying object values
    //MODIFIES ORIGINAL
copy[2].name = "Bob";
copy[3].push(30);

console.log(original[2].name); // Output: "Bob"
console.log(copy[2].name);     // Output: "Bob"
console.log(original[3]);      // Output: [10, 20, 30]
console.log(copy[3]);          // Output: [10, 20, 30]